        "sectionTitle": "TECHNICAL COMMUNICATION TRACK",
        "rawLine": "In the Technical Communication track, students learn to communicate complex information in a way that is concise, usable and compelling. Students learn how to identify the needs of an audience, design through an iterative process and make changes based on applied research. Courses emphasize real world design projects and students develop skills in collaborative problem solving and creativity. Technical Communication track students are well positioned for careers in technical and professional communication, user experience, usability, web design and other fields where communicating scientific and technical topics plays a central role. Students are encouraged to gain professional experience by completing internships and working with community partners.",
